text:
Dyckman Street, at, adjoining and west of the S.W. corner of Staff Street. Note a hot-dog stand on the corner, the 2 story shanty in the background and to the right a 2 story frame house.

October 26, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

Dyckman Street, west from Staff Street (seen in foreground) to the North (Hudson) River. Shown spanning this thoroughfare are the Henry Hudson Parkway structure and the New York Central Railroad bed. The first mentioned has just been completed and is a portion of the West Side Improvement Project which was opened to the public on October 12, 1937.

April 14, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
